quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,79,"So woe{1} to those who write the ",footnotes:1:[i.e., death and destruction.]
  2,80,"And they say, "
  2,81,"Yes, [on the contrary], whoever earns evil and his sin has encompassed him - those are the companions of the Fire; they will abide therein eternally."
  3,19,"Indeed, the religion in the sight of Allāh is Islām. And those who were given the Scripture did not differ except after knowledge had come to them - out of jealous animosity between themselves. And whoever disbelieves in the verses of Allāh, then indeed, Allāh is swift in [taking] account."
  3,20,"So if they argue with you, say, ",footnotes:1:[Those who had no scripture (i.e., the pagans).]
  3,21,"Those who disbelieve in the signs of Allāh and kill the prophets without right and kill those who order justice from among the people - give them tidings of a painful punishment."